|               struct timeval c;
|               int gettimeofday (struct timeval *restrict, void *restrict);

| int
| main ()
| {
| /* glibc uses struct timezone * rather than the POSIX void *
|                  if _GNU_SOURCE is defined.  However, since the only portable
